<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Alliliel on 05-30-2000 01:46 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">All I know is this- the more I spend time in the planes, the more I realize that clerics and enchanters are *SO* darn necessary. When you are tooling around in the Burning Woods or Lower Guk, you can take your pick, but you simply will NOT do these places with out them.

Last night's hate break was a fine example. We break in, first few groups get aggro and instakilled. Clerics couldnt camp out.

My group ports up and I start ressing. One of the poor folks I ressed who was a very fine person, but for some odd reason, was not paying attention, got to close to a wall and *presto* train again. I camp out.

I log in, there are TWO people in the plane of Hate, me and the rogue who hid. I start ressing, start with the chanters. Both of them are low on mana, we get a rat and an abhorrent, the lom chanters mez both mobs, they take turns medding while the other mezzes, just the 4 of us up there, and I'm medding for mana. I'm constantly camping, interrupting my self at 5 sec. The chanters cant med fast enough due to resists on mez.

I get some tanks ressed, they grab weapons only and I heal them, they fight one of the mobs. We win!

I get more people ressed, another train from someone getting too close to a wall. I camp out. Repeat the above 2 more times and you get the idea.

Once we got started tho, the loots were- rogue gloves, rogue legs, paladin shield, cleric gloves x2, cleric bracer, cleric boots, mage boots, mage arms, chanter arms, and lots of cash loots.

All in all, a very fine raid loot-wise, we had a TON of fun, and I was honored to have been a part of it, because the teamwork of the chanters was flawless and the rogue did such a fine job. 

Oh, and there were no druids.

So does that mean that clerics (and chanters too!) are too powerful? No. It means that each group has certain times when they will shine.

If I'm running around Burning Woods or Skyfire, a Druid is a fine addition to a group.

In SolB, Druid Charm can take a load off the chanter when it comes to the bats.

To sum up my post- blanket statements such as "Druids are worthless" or "Clerics are too powerful" are not particularly meaningful. There is a sense of context that is required to determine what makes an effective group or a class.

------------------
Alliliel Archfalcon
Cleric of Tunare
Consul of Initiates
The Sisters of Virtue
Tunare Server</TEXTAREA>
